2153E9539B05AD","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Water collection and preparation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"1D8E9119A5054CA0AFECE382FDEAA42D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Gently resuspend the cells from the filter using 1-2 ml sterile artificial sea water (ASW) and stain a 500 \u00b5l volume of the cell concentrate with 10 \u00b5M Paclitaxel, Oregon Green\u00ae 488 Conjugate (to target cytoskeletal tubulin). Incubate for 1 hour at room temperature.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"60F8A4B01A9B4D1EBA9848570A87C48D","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Use a 1:100 dilution of a 1 mM Paclitaxel, Oregon Green stock solution (prepared in DMSO and stored at -20\u00b0C).<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":717953,"guid":"9D95A6C040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","previous_id":758505,"previous_guid":"202FE84091A611E981DF699E813C3146","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A16605A195794688ADC21E7622C603C7","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Water collection and preparation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F988780EFDE84D9EB38D2D8EBF341853","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Also stain with 2 \u00b5g\/ml Hoechst 33342 (to target dsDNA) for 30 mins at room temperature.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"306C3B2040D211E99E35F59520C4F699","order_id":2,"type_id":20,"title":"reagents","source":{"id":181560,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Hoechst 33342","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.thermofisher.com\/order\/catalog\/product\/H1399","sku":"H1399","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Invitrogen - Thermo Fisher","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/www.thermofisher.com\/us\/en\/home\/brands\/invitrogen.html","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.iohttps:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.iohttps:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"id":191},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":717955,"guid":"A8A5128040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","previous_id":717957,"previous_guid":"A8A587B040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"59A7AE02FA0946F3AE6BEAAB33B734E6","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Flow cytometry and sorting"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"FF3D607AB90648A1B51C65331C6FD9C4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Use sort window combinations to select cells that show both green and blue fluorescence (520\/35 nm bandpass filter for Oregon Green [tubulin] and a 460\/50 nm bandpass filter for Hoechst 33342 [dsDNA]) compared to unstained control samples, and that show baseline red fluorescence (692\/40 nm bandpass filter) indicating the absence of chlorophyll. This will allow for the exclusion of the majority of photosynthetic cells.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"4EBF4432715A4F26A047DCF740FD72AC","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Regularly check the sort quality by sorting a known number of fluorescent beads onto a slide, and counting them on an epifluorescence microscope. Do not add beads to actual sort samples (to limit possibility for contamination).<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Please note that this protocol was performed using a BD Influx and it is possible that other cell-sorters would require different validation methods.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":717957,"guid":"A8A587B040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","previous_id":717958,"previous_guid":"A8A5AEC040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B0EC187B41854658AB7B77E015E189E4","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Flow cytometry and sorting"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"611BCC158EAC444F91F4F8819B98D35D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Perform cell sorting on a flow cytometer equipped with 488 nm and 355 nm lasers. Use sterile nuclease-free 1x PBS (pH 7.4) as sheath fluid.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"79E23B1040D211E99E35F59520C4F699","order_id":2,"type_id":20,"title":"reagents","source":{"id":181562,"mol_weight":0,"name":"PBS - Phosphate-Buffered Saline (10X) pH 7.4","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.thermofisher.com\/order\/catalog\/product\/AM9625","sku":"AM9625","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Invitrogen - Thermo Fisher","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/www.thermofisher.com\/us\/en\/home\/brands\/invitrogen.html","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.iohttps:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.iohttps:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"id":191},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":717958,"guid":"A8A5AEC040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","previous_id":717953,"previous_guid":"9D95A6C040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"023A22688C9E4AFBB76D1553982B9206","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Flow cytometry and sorting"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C450CF40F2FF4E80B9B9743F2DC12040","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Prior to sorting, illuminate 96-well plates by UV radiation inside the sort chamber (2 mins).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":717959,"guid":"A8A5AEC140CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","previous_id":717955,"previous_guid":"A8A5128040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EDA75386677C472DA6C0EB2B187AACDD","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Flow cytometry and sorting"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6322215A856549B6B2C33800E9DB4785","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Sort targeted cells into 96-well plates (one cell per well; Single-Cell sorting mode in BD FACS \u2018Sortware\u2019 software). Leave the outer column of wells empty for sheath-fluid only negative controls.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":717960,"guid":"A8E3A22040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","previous_id":717959,"previous_guid":"A8A5AEC140CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E20A5A36D6D64AF39FAA854A9382455E","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Flow cytometry and sorting"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"DDE284D731DF43559A738C268FC05D9F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Cover the plates with foil and place at -80\u00b0C immediately after the sort.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":717961,"guid":"BDB8E2A040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","previous_id":717960,"previous_guid":"A8E3A22040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0773CD362994401DB50C96E52B118FD9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA amplification for single cell genome or amplicon sequencing"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"E970E32593114E45A516B5675FE7B418","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">UV-treat all materials (except cell samples) in a HL-2000 HybriLinker (UVP) for 30-90 mins prior to conducting multiple displacement amplification (MDA).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":717962,"guid":"BDB957D040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","previous_id":758506,"previous_guid":"21FCCE2091A811E981DF699E813C3146","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1E1428C6B03C49FA9A86F9A2A4CA0127","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA amplification for single cell genome or amplicon sequencing"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"0D0C75C364774C0C93D6277166BB0AD8","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Lyse samples (both sorted cells and negative controls) for 10 mins at 65\u00b0C using buffer D2 from the REPLI-g Single Cell Kit (Qiagen), according to the manufacturer's instructions for amplification of genomic DNA from single cells.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"39AE318040E011E99E35F59520C4F699","order_id":2,"type_id":20,"title":"reagents","source":{"id":181563,"mol_weight":0,"name":"REPLI-g Single Cell Kit","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.qiagen.com\/gb\/shop\/sample-technologies\/dna\/genomic-dna\/repli-g-single-cell-kit\/#orderinginformation","sku":"150345","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Qiagen","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.qiagen.com\/us\/products\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.iohttps:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.iohttps:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"id":25},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":717963,"guid":"BDB97EE040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","previous_id":717962,"previous_guid":"BDB957D040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"197E65DB488049FDB7202F6CBDE47C3B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA amplification for single cell genome or amplicon sequencing"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"443B0A55ECFA4CDE889F1DAB97E79194","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">After neutralization, amplify samples using the REPLI-g kit in a final volume of 50 \u00b5l. Perform MDA reactions in a thermal cycler for 8 h at 30\u00b0C with the lid temperature set to 65-70\u00b0C. After amplification, aliquot samples as follows:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">a)<\/span><span> 2 \u00b5l diluted 100-fold for PCRs (see step 14; stored at -20\u00b0C)<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">b)<\/span><span> 20 \u00b5l kept as a backup (stored at -80\u00b0C)<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">c)<\/span><span> 28 \u00b5l (stored at -80\u00baC). Use 25 \u00b5l of this aliquot for sequencing (step 17)\n \n \n <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":717965,"guid":"BDB9CD0040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","previous_id":717963,"previous_guid":"BDB97EE040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D6466F3A30EC4FD4ADEBDAC7D4644603","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Screening MDA products by amplification of the V9 region of the nSSU rRNA gene"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"10468EB0956447B3A459DE2E244E7595","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Dilute an aliquot (2 \u00b5l) of each MDA product 100-fold in nuclease-free water and use 2-5 \u00b5l of this dilution as the template for 25 \u00b5l PCR reactions. Carry out PCR amplification using the primers:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">1389F (5\u2019-TTGTACACACCGCCC-3\u2019)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">1510R (5\u2019-CCTTCYGCAGGTTCACCTAC-3\u2019)<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Use Phusion High-Fidelity DNA Polymerase (NEB) in a 25 \u03bcl reaction volume, with 0.35 \u03bcM final concentration of each primer, 3% DMSO and 2X GC buffer.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Initial denaturation step of 98\u00b0C for 30 s<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Followed by 25 cycles of:<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">98\u00b0C for 10 s<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">57\u00b0C for 30 s<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">72\u00b0C for 30s<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Then a final elongation step of 72\u00b0C for 10 mins<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"FD7AA09093FA11E9A6FB077667F0957D","order_id":2,"type_id":20,"title":"reagents","source":{"id":780,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Phusion High-Fidelity DNA Polymerase - 100 units","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.neb.com\/M0530","sku":"M0530S","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"New England Biolabs","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.neb.com\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.iohttps:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/2.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.iohttps:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/2.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"id":2},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"296966365B1247799F093909FFA7B195","order_id":3,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Primers from Amaral-Zettler <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">et al.<\/span><span> (2009); PCR cycling conditions from Logares <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">et al.<\/span><span> (2014).<\/span><\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":717966,"guid":"BDB9F41040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","previous_id":717965,"previous_guid":"BDB9CD0040CB11E9A20C4BC8CC5FE3F2","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A2E2315EF03444BF9A502D30C5C8C01E","order_id":1,"t